"script": "Could you swim across a pool of liquid mercury? You might think you'd sink like a stone, but mercury is so dense you'd barely break the surface. Your whole body would float high, like a cork bobbing on water. But try to swim, and you'd find it nearly impossible, because the metal is thirteen times heavier than water and shoves back against every stroke. Then the real danger creeps in. Mercury releases an invisible vapor, and just breathing above the pool poisons your nerves. So you'd float there helplessly, slowly going numb, on a shimmering silver mirror that's quietly killing you.",
